  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "When using regex in the route matcher, one cannot use filters that change the request path (json-grpc transcoder for example). \r\n\r\nThe reason is this ASSERT:\r\nhttps://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/blob/01fef5ba2d09c3b501ee89b645998a47e70cd44d/source/common/router/config_impl.cc#L655\r\n\r\nThis assert makes sure the path still matches. the problem with it that this assert is performed even if the path does not need to be rewritten (which is checked in the base class: https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/blob/01fef5ba2d09c3b501ee89b645998a47e70cd44d/source/common/router/config_impl.cc#L380).\r\n\r\nTwo options come to mind on how to fix this:\r\n- option 1: remove the ASSERT\r\n- option 2: refactor out lines 380-383 to a method (needPathRewrite() ?) and call it in RegexRouteEntryImpl::finalizeRequestHeaders\r\n\r\nThoughts?\r\n",
